The different parts that make up an EntityPath.

A non-empty string.

Note that the contents of the string is NOT escaped, so escaping needs to be done when printing this using Self::escaped_string.

Because of this, EntityPathPart does NOT implement AsRef<str> etc, nor does it implement Display: you must explicitly chose either the escaped or the unescaped version of it.

In the file system analogy, this is the name of a folder.
